{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
If we look at the continuation, White will do a one space jump at 1, then Black can play the diagonal move of 2 to cover the White stone.  White plays 3 and takes the marked Black stone in return.

Up to Black 4 we can say \cf1\b this is a success for Black!\cf0\b0
\cf1\lang1042\b\f1\fs18
