;B[hj]LB[ce:1][gg:2][fj:3][fl:4][hj:5]CR[dg]C[Dia.4 The diagonal

Black 1 is also a good move.  It erases White's eye space in the area, and drives White out into the center with 2.

Black will then jump out with 3.  White can jump out as well and then Black can jump out and naturally connect with 5.
\lang1042\f1\fs18
\lang1033\f0\fs16 Like this, White's two stones at the top are looking like they'll be captured.  This means at least 70-80 points easy for Black.
